From: Andy Lutomirski <luto@amacapital.net>
Date: Wed, 8 Oct 2014 12:32:47 -0700
Subject: fs: Add a missing permission check to do_umount
Git-commit: a1480dcc3c706e309a88884723446f2e84fedd5b
Patch-mainline: v3.18-rc1
References: CVE-2014-7975 bnc#900392

Accessing do_remount_sb should require global CAP_SYS_ADMIN, but
only one of the two call sites was appropriately protected.

Fixes CVE-2014-7975.

Signed-off-by: Andy Lutomirski <luto@amacapital.net>
Acked-by: Miklos Szeredi <mszeredi@suse.cz>
---
 fs/namespace.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/fs/namespace.c
+++ b/fs/namespace.c
@@ -1274,6 +1274,8 @@ static int do_umount(struct mount *mnt,
 		 * Special case for "unmounting" root ...
 		 * we just try to remount it readonly.
 		 */
+		if (!capable(CAP_SYS_ADMIN))
+			return -EPERM;
 		down_write(&sb->s_umount);
 		if (!(sb->s_flags & MS_RDONLY))
 			retval = do_remount_sb(sb, MS_RDONLY, NULL, 0);
